						<div class="postbody">Oh, I have forgot about the controller registers in this area.
<br />
<br />Well, I have a ridiculous 'waste'-style solution on the ROM blocking: throw in an extra ROM. I.e. two 64K ROMs, address lines are connected together. The extra ROM contains flags for every single byte of the address space that enables or disables PRG ROM per location. Since we don't need lowest 5 bits, we can use a 2K ROM as the extra ROM. Of course, this is more like a fun thing to think of, not a very practical solution, but should be doable.</div>

