					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No logic would be required, just three ROMs - PRG, CHR, and the extra ROM. The extra ROM would be basically 9th bit ('enable') for every byte of PRG, like D0 of the extra ROM connected to OE or CS of the PRG ROM.
<br />
<br />Actually, it starts to look not that impractical, because price of the ROM chip is comparable with a CPLD, but you don't need extra tools to program that ROM, unlike CPLD.</div>

